result.execSummary:
The defendant Rosalind Katrina Mann was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Cocaine/Coca [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(c).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Rosalind Katrina Mann in court with attorney Gary S. Cirilli.  Defendant Rosalind Katrina Mann in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 9:17 AM. Called 15CF94 and 16CM72. Court has received the revocation and warrant. Cirilli has summary, no errors or ommissions. State moves to dismiss 16CM72 for stated reasons. Cirilli does not object. Court dismisses 16CM72. State asks that a witness be allowed to give testimony in regards to the defendant. Court allows. State calls Laura Zimbler. Zimbler sworn in at 9:20 AM. Direct exam by State. Zimbler excused at 9:23 AM. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - recommends 5 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 2 years of initial confinement followed by 3 years of Extended Supervision. Cirilli makes final argument prior to sentencing - recommends 6 months in FC jail (130 days credit). Mann makes statement, remorseful. Court sentences the defendant to the following: count #5 - 6 months in FC jail - credit for 136 days - good time allowed, turn any unpaid costs into civil judgment, right to appeal, adjourned.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Rosalind Katrina Mann in court with attorney Gary S. Cirilli.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 11:50 AM. State - resolved - 15CF94 - amend count #1 to misd possession of coccaine contrary to 961.41(3g)(c) - reads new penalty, unclassified misd, DRI counts #2, #3 and#4, plead to count #1 as amended with a $1000.00 fine plus court costs and plead to count #5 as alleged - withhold sentence and place on probation for 3 years with fine of $100 plus costs and DRI entire case on 15CF190, conditions of probation would include: AODA and follow thru, maintain absolute sobriety, no possession of alcohol and no entry into any taverns, bars or similar class B establishments, employment/school, 200 hours of community service. Cirilli and Mann agree. Court dismisses and reads in case #15CF190 entirely, DRI counts #2, #3 and #4 on 15CF94, amends count #1 on 15CF94 to misd possession of coccaine contrary to 961.41(3g)(c) - reads new charge and penalty. Mann pleads NC to count #1 as amended and #5 as alleged on 15CF94. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her constitutional rights by entering her plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing, follow joint recommendation. Cirilli makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Mann withholds comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following: count #1 - $1000.00 fine plus costs and surcharges totalling $2733.00 - take bonde posted - remainder due thru probation on count #5 - to be paid within the first year of probation; count #5 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 3 years with conditions of: $100.00 fine plus costs totalling $654.00 - paid thru probation and to be paid within the first year of probation, continue with AODA follow up and continue with parenting class and follow thru, attend at least one AA/NA or similar meeting per week, no possession or consumption of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, 200 hours of community service - to be completed within the first 2 years, credit for 130 days credit if revoked, submit DNA sample, no possesion of firearms, no voting rights, right to appeal, adjourned.
